Channel Fix (OpenChanfix) - Database Migrations

Migration files for openchanfix schema updates.

Naming Convention
-----------------
NNN_description.sql

Examples:
  001_add_chanop_timestamp.sql
  002_add_flags_column.sql
  003_create_channel_history_table.sql


Example Migration File
----------------------
ALTER TABLE chanOps ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS last_op_time TIMESTAMP;
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_chanops_last_op_time ON chanOps(last_op_time);


Checking Applied Migrations
----------------------------
To see which migrations have been applied to the openchanfix database:

  psql openchanfix -c "SELECT file FROM gnuworld_migrations WHERE module='openchanfix' ORDER BY applied_at;"


Automatic Migration Application
--------------------------------
Migrations are applied automatically when openchanfix starts. Simply:

  1. Place your migration file in this directory
  2. Restart gnuworld
  3. The migration will be automatically detected and applied

The migration system will log each migration as it's applied.
If a migration fails, gnuworld will exit with an error message.


For detailed documentation, see ../../doc/README.migrations
